The paper discusses the vulnerability/robustness of deep neural networks (DNNs) and proposes a new method for designing adversarial attacks. This topic is closely related to machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of natural gradient descent, which is a common optimization technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.CR, cs.AI, and cs.NE.
